To increase the availability of diagnostic tests and creating a data infrastructure for rapid sharing of results. The capacity for specific and sensitive diagnostic tests with same-day results, which should be widely available on an outpatient basis, is crucial for case identification, including those with asymptomatic or mild infections. Moving from interventions on large populations to interventions on individual cases to isolate infected persons requires sufficient capacity to test for:


   •

inpatients (with rapid diagnoses);


   •

health care personnel and those with essential roles (who are in contact with the public in terms of health and safety);


   •

people in close contact with confirmed cases;


   •

and ambulatory patients with symptoms.
